<subSubSection box="[199,838,1234,1259]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1234,1511]" box="[199,838,1234,1259]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,299,1234,1259]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Ecology.</emphasis>
Found in dead pocilloporid corals at 
<quantity box="[718,761,1235,1259]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" unit="m" value="3.0">3 m</quantity>
depth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="476" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1234,1511]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,610,1270,1295]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Distribution and previous records.</emphasis>
The first report was from Mazatlan, 
<collectingRegion box="[1024,1109,1270,1295]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<collectingCountry box="[1024,1109,1270,1295]" name="Mexico" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Mexico</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hancock" box="[1124,1293,1270,1295]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" refString="Hancock, A. (1867) Note on the excavating sponges; with descriptions of four new species. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 19, 229 - 242." type="journal article" year="1867">Hancock 1867</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation pageId="25" pageNumber="476" refString="Carballo, J. L., Cruz-Barraza, J. A. &amp; Gomez, P. (2004) Taxonomy and description of clionaid sponges (Hadromerida, Clionaidae) from the Pacific Ocean of Mexico. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 141, 353 - 397. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2004.00126. x" type="journal article">
Carballo 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">et al.</emphasis>
(2004)
</bibRefCitation>
found the species in the Mexican Pacific again, ranging from the north (
<collectingRegion box="[1066,1148,1307,1331]" country="Mexico" name="Sonora" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Sonora</collectingRegion>
) to the south (
<collectingRegion box="[1307,1397,1307,1331]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1867" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Pione" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="mazatlanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">P. mazatlanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not previously been located outside Mexican waters, and this is the first record for 
<collectingCountry box="[1312,1436,1342,1367]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<collectingRegion box="[1312,1376,1343,1367]" country="New Zealand" name="West Coast" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Costa</collectingRegion>
Rica
</collectingCountry>
and Central America (
<figureCitation box="[399,484,1378,1403]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1173,1195]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1435,193,1152]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 30.Distribution of Pione mazatlanensisin the study area." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1147271/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="476" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1234,1511]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1414,1439]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Remarks.</emphasis>
The microrhabdes, especially those long and helical microrhabdes are the characteristics that allow identify the species and distinguish from other 
<emphasis box="[706,779,1452,1475]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[706,775,1452,1475]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Pione" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">Pione</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The dimensions of the spicules from the specimens we reviewed, are similar to those described from the Mexican Pacific (
<bibRefCitation author="Carballo" box="[902,1131,1486,1511]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" refString="Carballo, J. L., Cruz-Barraza, J. A. &amp; Gomez, P. (2004) Taxonomy and description of clionaid sponges (Hadromerida, Clionaidae) from the Pacific Ocean of Mexico. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 141, 353 - 397. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2004.00126. x" type="journal article" year="2004">
Carballo 
<emphasis box="[1008,1064,1486,1511]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">et al.</emphasis>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
